      "role": "user",
      "content": "the \"journey\" thing sounds nice in a poem but it feels like a lie when you're actually living it. if the destination is just total erasure, then the journey is just a long, painful way to get to nothing. it feels more like we're just prolonging the inevitable for no reason. if a movie is going to end in a blank screen anyway, why watch the whole thing? wouldn't it be more logical to just skip to the end?",
